<subSubSection id="C350656FAE31FFA8FF753EA3FECDD4B7" box="[151,295,1472,1499]" pageId="7" pageNumber="560" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE31FFA8FF753EA3FECDD4B7" blockId="7.[151,563,1435,1499]" box="[151,295,1472,1499]" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">
(
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE31FFA8FF7D3EA3FEF5D4B7" box="[159,287,1472,1499]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 15–17" captionStart-1="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId-0="8.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionStartId-1="9.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox-0="[292,1288,187,1909]" captionTargetBox-1="[153,1423,186,1907]" captionTargetId-0="figure-23@8.[289,1299,181,1919]" captionTargetId-1="figure-18@9.[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId-0="8" captionTargetPageId-1="9" captionText-0="FIGURES 15–17. Oedalea wulingshana sp. nov. (male). 15. Adult habitus, lateral view; 16. Head, lateral view; 17. Wing." captionText-1="FIGURES 18–21. Oedalea wulingshana sp. nov. (male). 18. Genitalia, dorsal view; 19. Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 20. Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 21. Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598018" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598024" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6598018/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6598024/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">Figs 15–21</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C350656FAE31FFA8FF753D6BFC0DD7DE" pageId="7" pageNumber="560" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE31FFA8FF753D6BFC0DD7DE" blockId="7.[151,1437,1544,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE31FFA8FF753D6BFEF8D74E" bold="true" box="[151,274,1544,1570]" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Palpus dark brown. Antenna 1.2 times as long as head, dark brown except scape black; first flagellomere 7.0 times longer than wide. Eyes with enlarged dorsal ommatidia. Hairs on mesonotum somewhat dense, 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE31FFA8FAA43D4EFA81D72A" box="[1350,1387,1581,1606]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">acr</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE31FFA8FF753D33FF5BD706" box="[151,177,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">dc</emphasis>
not separated. Wing uniformly brownish. Pterostigma rather narrow, posterior margin far from R 
<subScript id="17CE34A1AE31FFA8FB143D01FAE5D71C" attach="left" box="[1270,1295,1634,1648]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">2+3</subScript>
. Halter dark brown with brown base. Basal bridge of epandrium rather narrow; right surstylus rather short, nearly as long as wide, apically widely obtuse; left surstylus about 2.0 times wider than long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C350656FAE31FFA5FF253DDFFF3AD2ED" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="563" pageId="7" pageNumber="560" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE31FFA8FF253DDFFE33D69A" blockId="7.[151,1437,1544,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE31FFA8FF253DDFFE74D7BA" bold="true" box="[199,414,1724,1750]" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE31FFA8FE4D3DDFFDEED7BB" box="[431,516,1724,1751]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–17" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[292,1288,187,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-23@8.[289,1299,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–17. Oedalea wulingshana sp. nov. (male). 15. Adult habitus, lateral view; 16. Head, lateral view; 17. Wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598018" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598018/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity id="4CB29B01AE31FFA8FD4D3DDFFCE3D7BB" box="[687,777,1724,1751]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="560" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity id="4CB29B01AE31FFA8FC443DDFFBEBD7BB" box="[934,1025,1724,1751]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="7" pageNumber="560" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
. Head (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE31FFA8FBBB3DDFFB47D7BB" box="[1113,1197,1724,1751]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–17" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[292,1288,187,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-23@8.[289,1299,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–17. Oedalea wulingshana sp. nov. (male). 15. Adult habitus, lateral view; 16. Head, lateral view; 17. Wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598018" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598018/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="4CB29B01AE31FFA8FB5C3DDFFAF2D7BB" box="[1214,1304,1724,1751]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="560" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
, black with gray pollinosity. Eyes brownish black, contiguous on frons, except dorsal ommatidia enlarged, dark brownish red; clypeus shiny black. Hairs and bristles on head black, lower occiput with brownish yellow hairs. Ocellar tubercle distinct with 2 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE31FFA8FEA53C4AFE8BD62E" box="[327,353,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">oc</emphasis>
and 2 posterior hairs; upper occiput with 5–6 slightly long postocular bristles slightly curved forward and inward. Antenna rather long, 1.2 times as long as head height, dark brown except scape black; scape without dorsal bristles; pedicel with circlet of black apical bristles; first flagellomere elongated, 7.0 times longer than wide, short dark brown pubescent; stylus dark brown, nearly thick spine-like, about 0.8 times as long as basal width of first flagellomere. Proboscis 0.6 times as long as head height, brown to dark brown with black hairs; palpus dark brown with black hairs.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF35666CAE3EFFA7FF753CF4FA9FD6DC" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598018" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6598018" box="[151,1397,1943,1968]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598018/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="561" startId="8.[151,264,1943,1967]" targetBox="[292,1288,187,1909]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE3EFFA7FF753CF4FA9FD6DC" blockId="8.[151,1397,1943,1968]" box="[151,1397,1943,1968]" pageId="8" pageNumber="561">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3EFFA7FF753CF4FEBED6C3" bold="true" box="[151,340,1943,1967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="561">FIGURES 15–17.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D67AE3EFFA7FEB83CFBFDD2D6DC" authority="Zeng &amp; Lin &amp; Yang, 2022" authorityName="Zeng &amp; Lin &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2022" box="[346,568,1944,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oedalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="561" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wulingshana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3EFFA7FEB83CFBFDD2D6DC" box="[346,568,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="561">Oedalea wulingshana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3EFFA7FDDC3CFBFD65D6DC" bold="true" box="[574,655,1944,1968]" pageId="8" pageNumber="561">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20D578DAE3EFFA7FDDC3CFBFD65D6DC" box="[574,655,1944,1968]" pageId="8" pageNumber="561" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(male). 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3EFFA7FD063CF4FCEED6C3" bold="true" box="[740,772,1943,1967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="561">15.</emphasis>
Adult habitus, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3EFFA7FBC63CF4FBAED6C3" bold="true" box="[1060,1092,1943,1967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="561">16.</emphasis>
Head, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3EFFA7FAF33CF4FADAD6C3" bold="true" box="[1297,1328,1943,1967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="561">17.</emphasis>
Wing.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF35666CAE3FFFA6FF753CF4FA72D6B8" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598024" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6598024" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598024/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" startId="9.[151,264,1943,1967]" targetBox="[153,1423,186,1907]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE3FFFA6FF753CF4FA72D6B8" blockId="9.[151,1436,1943,2004]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3FFFA6FF753CF4FEBFD6C3" bold="true" box="[151,341,1943,1967]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">FIGURES 18–21.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D67AE3FFFA6FEBF3CFBFDD6D6DC" authority="Zeng &amp; Lin &amp; Yang, 2022" authorityName="Zeng &amp; Lin &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2022" box="[349,572,1944,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oedalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wulingshana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3FFFA6FEBF3CFBFDD6D6DC" box="[349,572,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">Oedalea wulingshana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3FFFA6FDA13CFBFD7FD6DC" bold="true" box="[579,661,1944,1968]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20D578DAE3FFFA6FDA13CFBFD7FD6DC" box="[579,661,1944,1968]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(male). 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3FFFA6FD0C3CF4FCE7D6C3" bold="true" box="[750,781,1943,1967]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">18.</emphasis>
Genitalia, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3FFFA6FBE73CF4FBCFD6C3" bold="true" box="[1029,1061,1943,1967]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">19.</emphasis>
Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3FFFA6FF753CD8FF5DD6BF" bold="true" box="[151,183,1979,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">20.</emphasis>
Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3FFFA6FDDE3CD8FDB6D6BF" bold="true" box="[572,604,1979,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">21.</emphasis>
Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE3CFFA5FF253BF4FC2BD099" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1185]" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">
Thorax subshiny black with thin gray pollinosity. Hairs on thorax rather short, pale yellow; bristles dark brownish yellow; hairs on mesonotum uniform, somewhat dense; 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3CFFA5FCA13BD8FC87D1B8" box="[835,877,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">ppn</emphasis>
absent; 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3CFFA5FC2C3BD8FC19D1B8" box="[974,1011,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">acr</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3CFFA5FBCC3BD8FBA2D1B9" box="[1070,1096,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">dc</emphasis>
not separated; 2 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3CFFA5FAED3BD8FAD9D1B9" box="[1295,1331,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">npl</emphasis>
(anterior one short, posterior one long), 1 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3CFFA5FDE73BBCFDC6D194" box="[517,556,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">psa</emphasis>
, 1 long 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3CFFA5FD6A3BBCFD52D194" box="[648,696,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">prsc</emphasis>
; 3 pairs of 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3CFFA5FCDA3BBCFCA5D194" box="[824,847,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">sc</emphasis>
. Legs dark yellow to brownish yellow, except coxae nearly yellow, hind tibia blackish except base and tarsi from apex of tarsomere 1 blackish onward. Fore tibia slightly thickened, hind tibia slightly curved. Hairs and bristles on legs brown to dark brown; coxae with brownish yellow hairs and bristles. Fore femur slightly thickened, 1.2 times as wide as mid femur; hind femur distinctly thickened, 2.8 times as wide as mid femur, with row of rather long brownish pd on basal 3/5, with about four rows of black ventral spine-like bristles apically (outer 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3CFFA5FD8D3AF0FD63D0C0" box="[623,649,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">av</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3CFFA5FD273AF0FD35D0C0" box="[709,735,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">pv</emphasis>
rather long). Wing (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE3CFFA5FC2C3AF0FBF9D0C1" box="[974,1043,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1973,1997]" captionTargetBox="[273,1317,201,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[259,1328,181,1949]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Oedalea linzhiensis sp. nov. (male). 1. Adult habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, lateral view; 3. Wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598004" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598004/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) uniformly brownish; dark brown pterostigma long, oval, posterior margin far from R 
<subScript id="17CE34A1AE3CFFA5FD323AAAFD03D0BB" attach="left" box="[720,745,457,471]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">2+3</subScript>
; veins dark brown, R 
<subScript id="17CE34A1AE3CFFA5FC3A3AAAFC1BD0BB" attach="left" box="[984,1009,457,471]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">2+3</subScript>
weakly curved, M 
<subScript id="17CE34A1AE3CFFA5FB223AAAFB22D0BB" attach="left" box="[1216,1224,457,471]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">2</subScript>
complete. Squama dark yellow with dark yellow hairs. Halter dark brown with brown base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE3CFFA5FF253A9CFB40D351" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1185]" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">Abdomen nearly straight, somewhat shiny blackish with gray pollen. Hypopygium narrower than pregenital segments. Hairs and bristles on abdomen brownish yellow, except those on apex dark brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE3CFFA5FF253924FE63D255" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1185]" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">
Terminalia (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE3CFFA5FEAD3924FE38D30D" box="[335,466,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1423,186,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Oedalea wulingshana sp. nov. (male). 18. Genitalia, dorsal view; 19. Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 20. Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 21. Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598024" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598024/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">Figs 18–21</figureCitation>
): Left and right cerci (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE3CFFA5FD2F3924FCF4D30D" box="[717,798,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1423,186,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Oedalea wulingshana sp. nov. (male). 18. Genitalia, dorsal view; 19. Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 20. Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 21. Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598024" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598024/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) triangular and strongly narrowed. Basal bridge of epandrium (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE3CFFA5FF0B3908FED0D3E9" box="[233,314,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1423,186,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Oedalea wulingshana sp. nov. (male). 18. Genitalia, dorsal view; 19. Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 20. Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 21. Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598024" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598024/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) rather narrow; left and right epandrial lamellae (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE3CFFA5FC803908FC58D3E9" box="[866,946,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1423,186,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Oedalea wulingshana sp. nov. (male). 18. Genitalia, dorsal view; 19. Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 20. Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 21. Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598024" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598024/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) thick, not narrowed apically (dorsal view). Right epandrial lamella (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE3CFFA5FE5A39ECFDE7D3C5" box="[440,525,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1423,186,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Oedalea wulingshana sp. nov. (male). 18. Genitalia, dorsal view; 19. Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 20. Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 21. Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598024" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598024/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) somewhat trapezoidal (lateral view); right surstylus longer than wide, arched ventrally (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE3CFFA5FEE939D0FE8AD3A1" box="[267,352,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1423,186,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Oedalea wulingshana sp. nov. (male). 18. Genitalia, dorsal view; 19. Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 20. Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 21. Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598024" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598024/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
), basally with outer margin weakly incised, apically widely obtuse. Left epandrial lamella (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE3CFFA5FA8D39D0FF5ED39D" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1423,186,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Oedalea wulingshana sp. nov. (male). 18. Genitalia, dorsal view; 19. Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 20. Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 21. Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598024" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598024/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) somewhat trapezoidal (lateral view); left surstylus somewhat quadrate, short and wide (about 2.0 times wider than long), with straight apical margin (lateral view). Hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE3CFFA5FC6B3998FC30D279" box="[905,986,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–21" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1423,186,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 18–21. Oedalea wulingshana sp. nov. (male). 18. Genitalia, dorsal view; 19. Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 20. Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 21. Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598024" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598024/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) rather long; apical hook relatively long thick, weakly curved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE3CFFA5FF253820FF3AD2ED" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1185]" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3CFFA5FF253820FECFD231" bold="true" box="[199,293,835,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 3.7–4.0 mm, wing length 
<quantity id="4CB29B01AE3CFFA5FD053820FC99D231" box="[743,883,835,861]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="10" pageNumber="563" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="3.3">3.3–3.7 mm</quantity>
. Halter paler than male, brown with dark yellow base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
