<subSubSection id="C350656FAE3CFFA5FF253F78FA6DD511" pageId="10" pageNumber="563" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE3CFFA5FF253F78FA6DD511" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1185]" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3CFFA5FF253F78FED1D559" bold="true" box="[199,315,1051,1077]" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D67AE3CFFA5FCF63F78FC29D559" authority="Chvala" authorityName="Chvala" authorityYear="1983" box="[788,963,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oedalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="freyi">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3CFFA5FCF63F78FC80D559" box="[788,874,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">O. freyi</emphasis>
Chvála
</taxonomicName>
from Europe in having the eyes with enlarged dorsal ommatidia, but may be separated from the latter by the antennal stylus thick, spine-like and dark brown pterostigma. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D67AE3CFFA5FEAA3F00FE76D511" authorityName="Chvala" authorityYear="1983" box="[328,412,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oedalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="freyi">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3CFFA5FEAA3F00FE76D511" box="[328,412,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">O. freyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the antennal stylus is somewhat slender, and the pterostigma is indistinct (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDB4B15AE3CFFA5FB043F00FA90D511" author="Chvala, M." box="[1254,1402,1123,1149]" pageId="10" pageNumber="563" pagination="1 - 279" refId="ref5954" refString="Chvala, M. (1983) The Empidoidea (Diptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. II. General part. The families Hybotidae, Atelestidae and Microphoridae. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica, 12, 1 - 279." type="journal article" year="1983">Chvála 1983</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C350656FAE3CFFA5FF253FE4FBA4D5CD" box="[199,1102,1159,1185]" pageId="10" pageNumber="563" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE3CFFA5FF253FE4FBA4D5CD" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1185]" box="[199,1102,1159,1185]" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3CFFA5FF253FE4FEA4D5CD" bold="true" box="[199,334,1159,1185]" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the 
<typeStatus id="54F18846AE3CFFA5FD543FE4FD0CD5CD" box="[694,742,1159,1185]" pageId="10" pageNumber="563">type</typeStatus>
locality, Wulingshan Mountain.
</paragraph>
